oss.</small><br><small>\n''* Nadal received a walkover in the second round of the [[2019 US Open \u2013 Men's Singles|2019 US Open]], which does not count as a win.''</small>\n\n===Finals: 27 (19 titles, 8 runner-ups)===\n{| class=\"sortable wikitable\"\n! Result\n! Year\n! width=120 | Tournament\n! Surface\n! width=150 | Opponent\n! width=270 class=\"unsortable\" | Score\n|- style=\"background:#ebc2af\"\n| bgcolor=98fb98 | Win || [[2005 French Open \u2013 Men's Singles|2005]] || [[French Open]] || Clay || {{flagicon|ARG}} [[Mariano Puerta]] || 6\u20137<sup>(6\u20138)</sup>, 6\u20133, 6\u20131, 7\u20135\n|- style=\"background:#ebc2af\"\n| bgcolor=98fb98 | Win || [[2006 French Open \u2013 Men's Singles|2006]] || French Open <small>(2)</small> || Clay || {{flagicon|SUI}} [[Roger Federer]] || 1\u20136, 6\u20131, 6\u20134, 7\u20136<sup>(7\u20134)</sup>\n|- style=\"background:#cfc\"\n| bgcolor=ffa07a | Loss || [[2006 Wimbledon Championships \u2013 Men's Singles|2006]] || [[The Championships, Wimbledon|Wimbledon]] || Grass || {{flagicon|SUI}} Roger Federer || 0\u20136, 6\u20137<sup>(5\u20137)</sup>, 7\u20136<sup>(7\u20132)</sup>, 3\u20136\n|- style=\"background:#ebc2af\"\n| bgcolor=98fb98 | Win || [[2007 French Open \u2013 Men's Singles|2007]] || French Open <small>(3)</small> || Clay || {{flagicon|SUI}} Roger Federer || 6\u20133, 4\u20136, 6\u20133, 6\u20134\n|- style=\"background:#cfc\"\n| bgcolor=ffa07a | Loss || [[2007 Wimbledon Championships \u2013 Men's Singles|2007]] || Wimbledon || Grass || {{flagicon|SUI}} Roger Federer || [[2007 Wimbledon Championships \u2013 Men's singles final|6\u20137<sup>(7\u20139)</sup>, 6\u20134, 6\u20137<sup>(3\u20137)</sup>, 6\u20132, 2\u20136]]\n|- style=\"background:#ebc2af\"\n| bgcolor=98fb98 | Win || [[2008 French Open \u2013 Men's Singles|2008]] || French Open <small>(4)</small> || Clay || {{flagicon|SUI}} Roger Federer || 6\u20131, 6\u20133, 6\u20130\n|- style=\"background:#cfc\"\n| bgcolor=98fb98 | Win || [[2008 Wimbledon Champion