ublisher=BBC Sport|date=20 May 2007|accessdate=11 June 2012}}</ref>\n|-\n| 2004\u20132019 || 20 match wins against [[List of ATP number 1 ranked singles players|world No. 1]] players{{#tag:ref|The world No. 1 players who Nadal defeated were [[Roger Federer]] (13 times)<ref>{{cite web|title=Nadal\u2013Federer Head to Head|url=http://www.atpworldtour.com/Players/Head-To-Head.aspx?pId=N409&oId=F324|accessdate=10 September 2013|publisher=ATP World Tour|url-status=dead|archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20130814212515/http://www.atpworldtour.com/Players/Head-To-Head.aspx?pId=N409&oId=F324|archivedate=14 August 2013}}</ref> and [[Novak Djokovic]] (6 times).<ref>{{cite web|title=Nadal\u2013Djokovic Head to Head|url=http://www.atpworldtour.com/Players/Head-To-Head.aspx?pId=N409&oId=D643|accessdate=10 September 2013|publisher=ATP World Tour|url-status=dead|archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20110819042249/http://www.atpworldtour.com/Players/Head-To-Head.aspx?pId=N409&oId=D643|archivedate=19 August 2011}}</ref>|group=lower-alpha}} || '''Stands alone''' ||\n|-\n| rowspan=2 | 2002\u20132019 || 91.79% (436\u201339) clay court match winning percentage || '''Stands alone''' || <ref>{{cite web|title=FedEx ATP Reliability Index \u2013 Winning percentage on Clay|url=http://www.atpworldtour.com/Reliability-Zone/Reliability-Clay-Career-List.aspx|accessdate=18 March 2013|publisher=ATP World Tour}}</ref>\n|-\n| 84.73% (882\u2013159) outdoor match winning percentage || '''Stands alone''' || <ref>{{cite web|title=Performance Career Outdoor From All Countries|url=http://www.atpworldtour.com/en/performance-zone/win-loss-index/career/outdoor/all/|accessdate=11 May 2018|publisher=ATP World Tour}}</ref>\n|-\n| 2017\u20132018 || Won 50 consecutive sets on a single surface (clay) || '''Stands alone''' || <ref>{{cite web|title=50 And Counting...|url=http://www.atpworldtour.com/en/news/nadal-thiem-coric-madrid-2018-thursday|accessdate=10 May 2018|publisher=ATP World Tour}}</ref>\n|-\n| 2005\u20132018 || 11+ titles at a single tournament (French Open, Monte Carlo, Barcelona) || '''Stands alone''' || <ref name=FO10/>\n|-\n| 2005\u20132012 || 8 consecutive titles at a single tournament (Monte Carlo) || '''Stands alone''' || <ref>{{cite news|title=Rafael Nadal beats Novak Djokovic to win eighth consecutive Monte Carlo Masters title|url=https://www.telegraph.co.uk/sport/tennis/9219433/Rafael-Nadal-beats-Novak-Djokovic-to-win-eighth-consecutive-Monte-Carlo-Masters-title.html|date=22 April 2012|accessdate=23 April 2012|first=Simon|last=Briggs|work=The Daily Telegraph}}</ref>\n|-\n| 2004\u20132006 || 16 titles won as a teenager || [[Bj\u00f6rn Borg]] || <ref>{{cite news|url=http://www.atpworldtour.com/Tennis/Players/Top-Players/Rafael-Nadal.aspx|title=Rafael Nadal \u2013 Career Highlights|publisher=ATP World Tour|accessdate=14 June 2012|quote=2006 \u2013 Tied Borg with his 16th career teenage title in Rome, most in Open Era.}}</ref>\n|-\n| 2005\u20132019 || 37 clay court big titles || '''Stands alone''' ||\n|}\n===Professional awards===\n* [[ITF World Champions|ITF World Champion]]: 2008, 2010, 2017, 2019.\n* [[ATP Awards|ATP Player of the Year]]: 2008, 2010, 2013, 2017, 2019.\n\n== See also ==\n{{Portal|Tennis}}\n* [[Rafael Nadal career statistics]]\n* [[List of career achievements by Rafael Nadal]]\n* [[List of Grand Slam men's singles champions]]\n* [[All-time tennis records \u2013 men's singles]]\n* [[Open Era tennis records \u2013 men's singles]] (since 1968)\n* [[ATP World Tour records]] (since 1990)\n* [[List of ATP number 1 ranked singles tennis players]] (since 1973)\n* [[World number 1 ranked male tennis players]] (all time, based on recognized tennis authorities)\n* [[Tennis tournament records and statistics]]\n* [[List of Open Era tennis records]]\n* [[ATP World Tour Awards]]\n* [[Sports in Spain]]\n\n== Notes ==\n{{notelist|30em}}\n\n== References ==\n{{Reflist}}\n\n== External links ==\n{{sisterlinks|q=Rafael Nadal|c=Category:Rafael Nadal|n=no|b=no|v=no|voy=no|m=no|mw=no|wikt=no|s=no|species=no}}\n\n* {{official website|http://www.rafaelnadal.com/en/}} {{in lang|es}}\n\n=== Profiles ===\n\n* {{ATP|N409}}\n* {{ITF profile|100007935}}\n* {{DavisCup player|800226907}}\n* {{IMDb name|1755783}}\n\n{{Rafael Nadal start boxes}}\n{{Rafael Nadal}}\n{{Big Four (tennis)}}\n{{navboxes|title=Rafael Nadal in the [[grand slam (tennis)|Grand Slam]] tournaments\n|list1=\n{{Australian Open men's singles champions}}\n{{French Open men's singles champions}}\n{{Wimbledon men's singles champions}}\n{{US Open men's singles champions}}\n{{Tennis Career Grand Slam Champions}}\n{{Tennis men grand slam three and over}}\n{{Men's tennis players who won two or more Grand Slam singles titles in one calendar year}}\n}}\n{{navboxes|title=Rafael Nadal [[Rafael Nadal career statistics|achievements]]\n|list1=\n{{Tennis World Number Ones (men)}}\n{{Footer Olympic Champions Tennis Men}}\n{{Footer Olympic Champions Tennis Men's Doubles}}\n{{ATP Masters Series tournament winners}}\n{{ATP Masters Series tournament doubles winners}}\n{{Laureus World Sportsman of the Year}}\n{{Laureus World Sports Award for Comeback of the Year}}\n{{Spanish Sportsman of the Year}}\n{{Prince of Asturias Award for Sports}}\n{{Top ten tennis players|atpsingles=y}}\n{{Top ten male singles tennis players of countries belonging to Tennis Europe}}\n{{Top ten Spanish male singles tennis players}}\n}}\n{{Authority control}}\n\n{{DEFAULTSORT:Nadal, Rafael}}\n[[Category:1986 births]]\n[[Category:Australian Open (tennis) champions]]\n[[Category:Balearic tennis players]]\n[[Category:French Open champions]]\n[[Category:Grand Slam (tennis) champions in men's singles]]\n[[Category:Laureus World Sports Awards winners]]\n[[Category:Living people]]\n[[Category:Medalists at the 2008 Summer Olympics]]\n[[Category:Medalists at the 2016 Summer Olympics]]\n[[Category:Olympic gold medalists for Spain]]\n[[Category:Olympic medalists in tennis]]\n[[Category:Olympic tennis players of Spain]]\